1778516755321234	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvJg		item.create	bn-3gz	{"description":"Open ~/.cache/reckon/index.sqlite (create if missing). Run migrations for the two tables defined in notes/plan.md §8.\nUse rusqlite with the bundled feature. Bump a `schema_version` PRAGMA user_version so future schema changes are detectable.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-dcp","size":"s","title":"Cache schema migration: source_files + events"}	blake3:fV8jCEABs6ttRILewCyUQz9HhdLqBim3wSuPOjP0xoE
1778516755437278	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvJw		item.create	bn-hxj	{"description":"On first run (no cache rows), every Reader streams its events through the Sink, the aggregator batches into\ntransactions of ~5000 rows, INSERT OR IGNORE keyed by (source, dedup_key). Track files in source_files with their\nfinal (mtime, size, last_offset).\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-dcp","size":"s","title":"Cold scan: bulk insert events"}	blake3:tRXQZuPBl1S9O2DfxnwEjtgLHqEg1XGxOItdCzNqRF0
1778516755558434	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvKA		item.create	bn-3n4	{"description":"Before opening a JSONL file, look it up in source_files. If (mtime, size) match → skip. If size grew → open and\nseek to last_offset, parse only the new bytes, then update last_offset to the new size.\nPi's session-index.sqlite already gives us per-session last_modified; use it to skip whole sessions.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-dcp","size":"m","title":"Warm scan: stat skip + JSONL last_offset tail-resume"}	blake3:oiIYZa7nf0wQg7frINPvv7UzvRpPrMRcI5gDZUToX4s
1778516755672961	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvKQ		item.create	bn-2qk	{"description":"OpenCode: track max(created) in source_files (path = '<sqlite>'); on warm run query WHERE created > last_max.\nOpenRouter: never trust cache (30-day rolling window); always re-fetch and INSERT OR REPLACE on dedup_key.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-dcp","size":"s","title":"OpenCode warm path + OpenRouter cache bypass"}	blake3:QlbrWYuB7tj67qBXYNyOyUG52Xx4yl-UX0RODU0XAZI
1778516755789463	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvKg		item.create	bn-2v6	{"description":"Add a criterion bench or a simple `time cargo run --release -- --month 2026-04` regression test.\nAcceptance: warm run (cache populated) completes in under 200ms on a year of real data on this machine.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-dcp","size":"s","title":"Bench: warm run under 200ms on a year of data"}	blake3:faGNo1lVpiYMpxTN-d5KznD2IWNycpaSQY1kqBo098I
1778516755908035	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvKw		item.create	bn-vcy	{"description":"GET https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BerriAI/litellm/main/model_prices_and_context_window.json via the asupersync HTTP client.\nCache at ~/.cache/reckon/pricing.json with mtime checked against a 7-day TTL. Failure to fetch falls back to the cached file,\nthen to the vendored fallback. Never block startup more than ~500ms on this; do it lazily / in parallel with the scan.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-25e","size":"s","title":"LiteLLM fetcher + 7-day TTL cache"}	blake3:HGs4aTONGBjW0hX2eI2XWmPYdVrxU07OemmSueXPU20
1778516756020474	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvLA		item.create	bn-1re	{"description":"--offline disables the LiteLLM HTTP call entirely. Pricing comes from ~/.cache/reckon/pricing.json (if present)\nelse the vendored fallback. Document the trade-off (older prices for newer models = $0 with a warning).\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-25e","size":"xs","title":"--offline flag wiring"}	blake3:Y038r0W_700uFXzLAM8yWBlWlbHASxAcuHKg0N5QsvI
1778516756137581	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvLQ		item.create	bn-3e9	{"description":"`cargo xtask vendor-pricing` re-downloads the LiteLLM JSON and writes it to crates/reckon-core/assets/pricing-fallback.json.\nRun on demand pre-release to bump the fallback.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-25e","size":"xs","title":"xtask vendor-pricing refresh command"}	blake3:OO1tUR4aBZr406yuxcSvlcboKD6nXWsXckXakSCRpqw
1778516756254122	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvLg		item.create	bn-1sk	{"description":"Track every unknown slug seen during a run. After the table, print one line:\n'Unknown pricing for: model-a, model-b, model-c (priced at $0)'. No noise per-event.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-25e","size":"xs","title":"Unknown-model collapsed warning"}	blake3:zEinbjQoQZfAJlRvfmrH4jEcvtMbqlYpxYNXhLii0a0
1778516756369549	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvLw		item.create	bn-ojx	{"description":"clap derives. Accept YYYY-MM. Validate ordering when both --since and --until set. Default (no flags) = every month\npresent in the cache, newest first.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"xs","title":"--month, --since, --until parsing"}	blake3:JXW4yOKHo6eDOntKhPCLnlAuKQ8QfwxCEjyX5cCIPYM
1778516756482289	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvMA		item.create	bn-3rz	{"description":"Comma-separated list: claude,codex,gemini,pi,opencode,openrouter. Validate against the Source enum. Default = all auto-detected.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"xs","title":"--source filter"}	blake3:o_MJNTAI_oEtbXdLud6nZOkzQ_l74hhXoV1fmhatanM
1778516756601115	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvMQ		item.create	bn-2q8	{"description":"Compose multi-key group-by. Default --by source,model. Renderer collapses missing dimensions (e.g. --by source hides the model column).\nPer-month total row always shown.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"s","title":"--by source|model|provider|project breakdown"}	blake3:u5uDHlYNmiJ6333OjQlR-PGrvHmCQhvapUZdAAcnOQk
1778516756716246	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvMg		item.create	bn-3r7	{"description":"Emit one JSON array of {month, source, model, provider, project, input, output, cache_read, cache_write, reasoning, cost_usd}.\nStable key order. Suppress all chrome (no banner, no warnings on stdout — warnings go to stderr).\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"xs","title":"--json output format"}	blake3:kMXfJ9NK8iBxoFmw0pOW73T8ugQCEYOEcExIDCoetFU
1778516756838823	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvMw		item.create	bn-l6s	{"description":"Default: colour if stdout is a TTY, else plain. --no-color overrides. NO_COLOR env respected.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"xs","title":"--no-color + TTY auto-detect"}	blake3:BFcUmPLpfcjoGzetECLoHoQtcAmcsDCHe5LBBTrSGoA
1778516756957348	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvNA		item.create	bn-3rj	{"description":"With the anonymised fixtures in tests/fixtures/<source>/, snapshot the rendered table for a single fixed month using\ninsta. Snapshot the --json form too. Use insta's redaction features to ignore wall-time-dependent fields.\n","kind":"task","parent":"bn-pso","size":"s","title":"insta snapshot tests on the fixture set"}	blake3:0y9rMjivNLA8zUJsFE5KhRulU1MAI9GSkm4jbjckIkQ
1778523470647081	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvNQ		item.update	bn-3rj	{"field":"description","value":"-"}	blake3:TUSFm5r_71p4hDniZsNzKloffMzsaaeu45y8WtN-0lI
1778523477770005	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvNg		item.update	bn-3rj	{"field":"description","value":"With the anonymised fixtures in tests/fixtures/<source>/, snapshot the rendered table for a single fixed month using insta. Snapshot the --json form too. Use insta's redaction features to ignore wall-time-dependent fields."}	blake3:u_HYmwEUFWUXd7Ju9-h9wqTrWIZVhcDC95UFf5Hktlk
1778523760213887	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvNw		item.update	bn-1y7	{"field":"title","value":"Monthly table renderer + M1 end-to-end demo"}	blake3:FEqhYhR8cJ_ThGzAhJfNAhw4BNLA-y9jMwmNoAg-gjs
1778523760224266	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvOA		item.update	bn-1y7	{"field":"description","value":"The M1 value delivery: cargo run prints the monthly table.\n\nScope:\n- crates/reckon-cli/src/report.rs aggregator: groups Vec<UsageEvent> into BTreeMap<(YearMonth, Source, ModelSlug), Aggregate> with one synthesised per-month TOTAL row.\n- crates/reckon-cli/src/render.rs uses tabled to render the layout in notes/plan.md section 2 (Month, Source, Model, In, Out, Cache, Reason, Cost columns; comma-separated thousands; $X.XX cost; - for unsupported token classes).\n- main() composes: build_readers (Claude only for M1) -> run_readers -> aggregate -> render to stdout.\n\nAcceptance:\n- cargo run on the users real ~/.claude data prints at least one month with non-zero cost.\n- Output spot-checked against ccusage daily totals summed to month: within 1 percent.\n- Empty input (no Claude data) prints \"No usage events found.\" and exits 0.\n- Per-month TOTAL row matches the column-wise sum of that months rows exactly."}	blake3:M5IQVKxuT_SuGwGN91tIDlwt7Mn2U8KUJ7HnexaFU6I
1778523760238910	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvOQ		item.update	bn-ive	{"field":"description","value":"Bootstrap the Cargo workspace and the no-op binary that proves asupersync is wired correctly.\n\nScope:\n- Workspace Cargo.toml with members: crates/reckon-core, crates/reckon-readers, crates/reckon-cli, crates/xtask.\n- reckon-cli depends on asupersync = { version = \"0.2\", features = [\"tls\", \"tls-webpki-roots\", \"proc-macros\"] }.\n- main() opens asupersync::Runtime::native(), enters a root region, returns Ok(()).\n- .gitignore: target/, .cargo/, *.swp.\n- scripts/check-no-tokio.sh greps cargo tree for forbidden crates; called from a build.rs or a cargo test.\n\nAcceptance:\n- cargo check --workspace passes with zero warnings.\n- cargo run -p reckon-cli exits 0 within 200ms.\n- cargo tree -p reckon-cli does NOT contain any of: tokio, hyper, reqwest, tower, axum, async-std, smol.\n- scripts/check-no-tokio.sh exits 0 today and exits non-zero if any forbidden crate is added."}	blake3:eZf0KSO5t9jmzkSXglFBN9Ybt-xETc4kRaQdsJaD0PA
1778523760261179	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvOg		item.update	bn-l2x	{"field":"description","value":"The data model every Reader emits and the aggregator consumes.\n\nScope:\n- crates/reckon-core/src/lib.rs exporting: Source (enum: Claude, Codex, Gemini, Pi, OpenCode, OpenRouter), UsageEvent (struct in notes/plan.md section 5), TokenCounts (input/output/cache_read/cache_write/reasoning, all u64), ModelSlug (newtype String), YearMonth (i32 year, u8 month 1-12).\n- YearMonth::from_utc(ts), ::next(), ::prev() for range iteration.\n- crates/reckon-core/src/model_map.rs with fn canonical(source: Source, raw: &str, provider: Option<&str>) -> ModelSlug. Default body: ModelSlug(raw.into()). Each reader milestone extends the match.\n- serde Serialize+Deserialize on all public types.\n- TokenCounts has total() and AddAssign for aggregation.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Unit tests: 2025-12-31T23:59:59Z and 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z parse to different YearMonths; year rollover works.\n- A UsageEvent round-trips through serde_json::to_string -> from_str unchanged (proptest).\n- model_map::canonical with no extensions returns the input verbatim wrapped in ModelSlug."}	blake3:bkelgrtBJw5AhGPP9Ul8poigQVIHMTu_aVl2PaCa1jc
1778523760282853	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvOw		item.update	bn-d7t	{"field":"description","value":"Async plumbing that drives readers in parallel under one asupersync region.\n\nScope:\n- trait Reader: Send + Sync { fn source(&self) -> Source; async fn scan(&self, cx: &Cx, sink: &Sink) -> Outcome<(), ReaderError>; fn cache_strategy(&self) -> CacheStrategy; }\n- Sink wraps asupersync::channel::mpsc::Sender<UsageEvent> (bounded 1024). Methods: send(event), close().\n- fn run_readers(cx, readers: Vec<Box<dyn Reader>>) -> Vec<UsageEvent>: opens a region, spawns one task per reader, drains receiver, returns when region quiesces.\n- CacheStrategy enum { JsonlTail, SqlCursor, NeverCache } returned by each reader for M5.\n\nAcceptance:\n- MockReader (emits 100 fixed-seed events) runs end-to-end under LabRuntime; output deterministic across runs.\n- Cancelling the parent Cx mid-scan: scan returns Cancelled; region closes cleanly; no leaked tasks (verified via asupersync probe).\n- Two readers in parallel: receiver gets all events from both (no drops when the bound saturates and both block on send)."}	blake3:2FMvXgXsMNpfXjKm6hgJjX6FgHDtw27Q3FZNYLTw3Ew
1778523760302235	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvPA		item.update	bn-1y6	{"field":"description","value":"First real reader. Reads ~/.claude/projects/<encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl and emits UsageEvents. Also extends model_map for anthropic/*.\n\nScope:\n- Walk ~/.claude/projects/*/ for *.jsonl (env CLAUDE_HOME overrides root).\n- Stream-parse each line with memchr; only handle objects where type == \"assistant\" and message.usage exists.\n- Token map: input_tokens -> input, output_tokens -> output, cache_creation_input_tokens -> cache_write, cache_read_input_tokens -> cache_read. reasoning = 0.\n- model from message.model; provider = \"anthropic\"; project = decode - to / on parent dir name.\n- timestamp parsed as UTC; month via YearMonth::from_utc.\n- dedup_key = requestId (Sink dedups across the run).\n- Extend model_map::canonical(Source::Claude, raw, _): claude-opus-4-7-* -> anthropic/claude-opus-4.7; claude-sonnet-4-6-* -> anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6; claude-haiku-4-5-* -> anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5. Strip the trailing date.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Fixture tests/fixtures/claude/sample.jsonl with 3 assistant turns (one with cache_read > 0) yields the golden Vec<UsageEvent>.\n- A fixture with one requestId appearing twice across two project dirs yields ONE event after dedup.\n- Real ~/.claude data parses without panic in under 5s.\n- All three Claude slug families on this machine map to a canonical anthropic/* slug."}	blake3:OX1pjDFdSgPqHgLFznoU6etDGAHygNuJEN4JMHfYq7E
1778523760322642	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvPQ		item.update	bn-l2h	{"field":"description","value":"Static pricing data + the formula that turns TokenCounts into USD.\n\nScope:\n- crates/reckon-core/assets/pricing-fallback.json: current LiteLLM model_prices_and_context_window.json snapshot, downloaded once for v1. M6 adds the xtask refresher.\n- struct Pricing { input_per_token, output_per_token, cache_read_per_token, cache_write_per_token, reasoning_per_token: Option<f64> } keyed by canonical slug.\n- fn load_pricing(path: &Path) -> HashMap<ModelSlug, Pricing>.\n- fn cost(tokens: &TokenCounts, p: &Pricing) -> f64 per notes/plan.md section 7.\n- Missing cache rates default to 0. Missing reasoning rate falls back to output_per_token.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Unit tests pin 3 known (model, tokens) -> cents pairs hand-computed from real LiteLLM data: anthropic/claude-opus-4.7, openai/gpt-5.2, google/gemini-2.5-pro. Tolerance ±$0.001.\n- Loading pricing-fallback.json takes < 50ms and yields >= 150 entries.\n- pricing-fallback.json is checked in to git so a fresh clone has working pricing without network."}	blake3:yiR-mq1-c7z4UNjxQYGDfZ-w6A30UiPfa0BW6ti0pjY
1778523760350313	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvPg		item.update	bn-fby	{"field":"description","value":"First half of the Pi reader: figure out which JSONL files to read.\n\nScope:\n- Try ~/.pi/agent/sessions/session-index.sqlite read-only.\n- If present AND its mtime is newer than every *.jsonl under sessions/, enumerate via SELECT path, id, cwd, timestamp, last_modified FROM sessions.\n- Else fall back to walkdir over ~/.pi/agent/sessions/<encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl.\n- Yield (session_path, session_id, cwd, last_modified) tuples to the parser stage (bn-37d).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Temp-dir test with 2 session files + a fresh session-index.sqlite returns both in < 100ms via the SQLite path.\n- Same temp dir with the sqlite deleted returns the same 2 tuples via walkdir.\n- Same temp dir with the sqlite touched older than the JSONLs falls back to walkdir.\n- Missing ~/.pi entirely returns 0 tuples (not an error)."}	blake3:VDSUduHFhdlWoDgdbNMGpQE9YdIPoGKRGCYNyK1z9W8
1778523760370200	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvPw		item.update	bn-37d	{"field":"description","value":"Second half of the Pi reader: extract UsageEvents from the JSONL.\n\nScope:\n- For each line: parse JSON. Match objects where type == \"message\" AND message.role == \"assistant\" AND message.usage is present.\n- Tokens: usage.input -> input; usage.output -> output; usage.cacheRead -> cache_read; usage.cacheWrite -> cache_write. reasoning = 0 (Pi does not separate it).\n- IGNORE message.usage.cost — Pi bakes in its own discounts; we compute unsubsidized cost via M1 pricing.\n- provider from message.provider; model from message.model. Compose canonical slug via model_map::canonical(Source::Pi, model, Some(provider)) — actual mapping ships in bn-26r.\n- timestamp from message.timestamp (epoch ms) -> UTC.\n- project = decode - to / on the parent sessions/<encoded-cwd> dir.\n- dedup_key = format!(\"{session_id}:{message.id}\").\n\nAcceptance:\n- Fixture tests/fixtures/pi/sample.jsonl (anonymised) parses to a known Vec<UsageEvent>.\n- Real ~/.pi/agent/sessions data parses without panic.\n- A session with zero assistant-with-usage messages emits zero events and returns Ok.\n- Pi cost block in the input is verifiably absent from the output (no f64 fields leak from raw input)."}	blake3:HquNla4QklhogbyUJGkLM_FVvt6p1__6wfnoUHlZCrI
1778523760391792	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvQA		item.update	bn-1ao	{"field":"description","value":"Walk the date-partitioned Codex tree and yield session files chronologically.\n\nScope:\n- Root: env CODEX_HOME or ~/.codex; scan <root>/sessions/YYYY/MM/DD/rollout-*-<uuid>.jsonl.\n- Skip non-matching filenames (logs_2.sqlite stays untouched for v1).\n- Yield (path, session_uuid_from_filename, date_from_dirs) tuples in chronological order.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Temp-dir test mirroring the YYYY/MM/DD partition structure with rollouts on 3 days returns files oldest-first.\n- Partial trees (missing DD subdirs) are tolerated; no panic.\n- A dir with a mix of rollout-*.jsonl and stray files yields only the rollouts.\n- Filename regex correctly extracts the UUID portion after rollout-YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS-."}	blake3:54NGGgICHffjrosnfpCZvekGnW7mj78Jf9IqydBrID4
1778523760411956	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvQQ		item.update	bn-3k3	{"field":"description","value":"Codex emits cumulative token totals; convert to per-turn deltas while tracking the active model.\n\nScope:\n- Per-file state: previous_totals: TokenCounts (zeros); active_model: Option<String> (None); session_id: Option<String>; turn_index: u32 (0).\n- payload.type == \"session_meta\": reset previous_totals; capture session_id; turn_index = 0.\n- payload.type == \"turn_context\": switch active_model.\n- payload.type == \"token_count\": delta = max(0, current - previous) per field; emit UsageEvent if any delta > 0; update previous; turn_index += 1.\n- Field map: input_tokens -> input, cached_input_tokens -> cache_read, output_tokens -> output, reasoning_output_tokens -> reasoning. cache_write = 0 (Codex does not expose it).\n- Sessions whose first token_count event is missing entirely (pre-2025-09-06 builds) are skipped silently.\n- dedup_key = format!(\"{session_id}:{turn_index}\"); model passes through model_map::canonical(Source::Codex, raw, None).\n\nAcceptance:\n- proptest: given a strictly-increasing cumulative sequence with arbitrary mid-session model changes, the sum of emitted deltas equals the final cumulative totals.\n- proptest: if a token_count event reports values smaller than previous (model reset), delta clamps to 0 (no negative emission).\n- Fixture tests/fixtures/codex/rollout-sample.jsonl with 3 turns + one mid-session model change yields a known Vec<UsageEvent>.\n- A rollout file missing any token_count is skipped (zero events) without warning to stderr."}	blake3:ar4ov3G_v6I-02atz7PMHpI0EeoPOwPFyDeTHNS6xaI
1778523760433018	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvQg		item.update	bn-26r	{"field":"description","value":"Extend model_map::canonical for Codex (OpenAI) and Pi slug families.\n\nScope:\n- Codex/OpenAI: strip date suffix. gpt-5.2-2025-* -> openai/gpt-5.2; gpt-4.1-2025-* -> openai/gpt-4.1; o1-2024-* -> openai/o1; o3-mini-2025-* -> openai/o3-mini. Pass through anything else verbatim.\n- Pi: when provider is present, compose \"{provider}/{normalised_model}\" where normalised_model collapses the version hyphens (claude-haiku-4-5 -> claude-haiku-4.5; claude-sonnet-4-6 -> claude-sonnet-4.6).\n- Cover every slug seen in the users actual sessions on this machine (audit via a one-liner script).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Unit tests: 4 OpenAI slug variants and 3 Pi (provider, model) pairs (including provider=openrouter passthrough).\n- After integration, running the M1 binary across all sources shows no \"Unknown pricing\" warnings for the top 5 most-used models on this machine.\n- Unknown OpenAI/Pi slug not in the map passes through verbatim, triggering the warning line (not a crash)."}	blake3:TyWG38A6XWEkeoy8CnGJDttZc0U76FaauXIWFB9WlbY
1778523760452678	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvQw		item.update	bn-8ou	{"field":"description","value":"Read Google Gemini CLI session JSON.\n\nScope:\n- Walk ~/.gemini/tmp/<hash>/chats/session-*.json (env GEMINI_HOME overrides root).\n- Each file is a JSON document with messages: []. Per assistant message:\n  - usageMetadata.promptTokenCount -> input\n  - usageMetadata.candidatesTokenCount -> output\n  - usageMetadata.cachedContentTokenCount -> cache_read\n  - usageMetadata.thoughtsTokenCount -> reasoning\n  - model from message metadata (fallback: session header)\n- provider = \"google\"; project = first 8 chars of <hash>; opportunistically consult ~/.gemini/projects.json to map hash -> cwd if listed.\n- timestamp: per-message ts when present; else session filename ts + per-message index offset.\n- dedup_key = format!(\"{session_filename}:{message_index}\").\n- Missing/empty usageMetadata: skip the message (not an error).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Fixture tests/fixtures/gemini/session-sample.json yields a known Vec<UsageEvent>.\n- Real ~/.gemini/tmp data parses without panic.\n- A hash listed in ~/.gemini/projects.json gets the human path in the project column; one not listed shows the 8-char hash.\n- Messages without usageMetadata are silently skipped."}	blake3:eA8PGGFf2hGyHdgn9gs1GSXbCbnwElVtUFVIUYB6R0M
1778523760474350	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvRA		item.update	bn-34n	{"field":"description","value":"Stream message rows from ~/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db without loading the 1.6 GB DB into memory.\n\nScope:\n- rusqlite::Connection::open_with_flags(path, SQLITE_OPEN_READONLY | SQLITE_OPEN_URI).\n- Prepared statement: SELECT id, session_id, tokens_input, tokens_output, tokens_reasoning, tokens_cache_read, tokens_cache_write, model_id, provider_id, created FROM message WHERE created > ?1 ORDER BY created LIMIT 1000.\n- Page until a page returns < LIMIT rows.\n- Emit one UsageEvent per row with any non-zero token field; dedup_key = message.id (UUID).\n- model via model_map::canonical(Source::OpenCode, model_id, Some(provider_id)).\n- timestamp = created (epoch ms).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Fixture SQLite with 5000 rows is processed in < 500ms; peak RSS delta < 50 MB.\n- A row with all token columns zero is skipped (not emitted).\n- The users real opencode.db (1.6 GB on this machine) is read without OOM and within a few seconds.\n- Schema mismatch (missing a column) returns a typed error, not a panic."}	blake3:vEcFYRrrH6m-6sostvk-0uceHZ1nxA1Gq_e5iiknpFc
1778523760495112	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvRQ		item.update	bn-pe5	{"field":"description","value":"Handle the cases where the SQLite path does not work.\n\nScope:\n- If ~/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db does NOT exist: walk ~/.local/share/opencode/storage/message/<sid>/*.json (one JSON file per message; same token field names under message-shape).\n- If the DB exists but rusqlite returns SQLITE_BUSY after one 50ms retry: log a single stderr line \"opencode: DB locked, skipping\" and return Ok from scan. Do not fail the whole reckon invocation.\n- No /tmp copy in v1.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Fixture with no DB + 3 storage/message/<sid>/*.json files yields the right Vec<UsageEvent>.\n- A flock-locked DB during a test produces the single warning line and Ok(()).\n- Missing opencode dir entirely (no DB, no storage/) returns 0 events without warning."}	blake3:YzNpmvIzZmFyjbd_4FSbVSbE2AWTHqEtjv9u8OF08Ho
1778523760517774	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvRg		item.update	bn-32h	{"field":"description","value":"Extend model_map::canonical for Gemini and OpenCode.\n\nScope:\n- Gemini: gemini-2.5-pro -> google/gemini-2.5-pro; gemini-2.5-flash-* -> google/gemini-2.5-flash; gemini-1.5-* preserved as-is under google/.\n- OpenCode: model_id is usually already vendor/model (openai/gpt-5.2, anthropic/claude-opus-4.7) — pass through. If it lacks a slash, compose with provider_id: format!(\"{provider_id}/{model_id}\").\n\nAcceptance:\n- Unit tests: 3 Gemini variants, 3 OpenCode forms (slashed and bare).\n- Running with Gemini+OpenCode sources shows no \"Unknown pricing\" warnings for the top 5 models on this machine."}	blake3:EgLdEV2qKXrSM3Jn0cg8fazVlqIx_WvZ4gUF9T-VDTk
1778523760536641	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvRw		item.update	bn-yl3	{"field":"description","value":"Stand up the asupersync HTTP client and the key-resolution chain.\n\nScope:\n- HttpClientBuilder with .tls_webpki_roots() and .user_agent(format!(\"reckon/{}\", env!(\"CARGO_PKG_VERSION\"))).\n- fn resolve_key() -> Option<String>: try RECKON_OPENROUTER_KEY env, then OPENROUTER_API_KEY env, then read ~/.config/reckon/config.toml field openrouter.key. Return None if nothing found.\n- fn mask_key(k: &str) -> \"sk-or-...XXXX\" (last 4 chars only). Used in every error message.\n- NEVER log or include the unmasked key in any output, ever.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Unit test: only OPENROUTER_API_KEY set -> resolve_key returns it.\n- Unit test: RECKON_OPENROUTER_KEY and OPENROUTER_API_KEY both set -> RECKON_OPENROUTER_KEY wins.\n- A grep for the unmasked key string in captured stdout+stderr across the test suite returns zero hits.\n- Client builder compiles with only asupersync features (no tokio reachable in cargo tree)."}	blake3:DKIMSXi0RCBzofFDXwtecnVeP4RfhKyptaDcfkNco_c
1778523760557294	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvSA		item.update	bn-2fs	{"field":"description","value":"Fetch OpenRouter activity history and emit UsageEvents.\n\nScope:\n- Loop dates from (today UTC - 29) to today UTC inclusive. For each: GET https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/activity?date=YYYY-MM-DD with Authorization: Bearer <key>.\n- Parse data: []. Per row: model (already vendor/model form, no remap), provider_name, prompt_tokens -> input, completion_tokens -> output, reasoning_tokens -> reasoning, usage -> known_cost_usd (extra field on UsageEvent; NOT the cost we render), byok_usage_inference -> also kept.\n- cache_read = cache_write = 0 (activity endpoint does not expose them).\n- dedup_key = format!(\"openrouter:{date}:{endpoint_id}\").\n- All 30 requests issued under one asupersync region; bounded concurrency of 4 in-flight via Semaphore.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Stub HTTP server returning fixture JSON across 30 dates: reader emits the expected events; known_cost_usd preserved on each.\n- Successful run completes in < 3s against the real API on a typical connection.\n- A day with HTTP 200 but data: [] is a no-op (no events, no error).\n- Backpressure: with concurrency=4, only 4 in-flight sockets at any moment (verified via asupersync probe)."}	blake3:9J9BtpCv1eCrLGLnTDt6pYdywecxJLa3al9fVQTOxjg
1778523760577533	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvSQ		item.update	bn-33k	{"field":"description","value":"Show the OpenRouter balance under the table.\n\nScope:\n- GET https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/credits with the bearer.\n- Response shape: { data: { total_credits, total_usage } }.\n- struct OpenRouterSummary { total_credits: f64, total_usage: f64, fetched_at: DateTime<Utc> }.\n- Rendered as a single trailing line when openrouter is in --source: \"OpenRouter balance: $X.XX (used $Y.YY of $Z.ZZ purchased)\".\n- Only fetched when openrouter is active (or a key resolves and default-source includes openrouter).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Stub server test: balance line matches the rendered string for a known response.\n- 401 from /credits is routed through the same handler as /activity (see bn-131).\n- --json includes the summary as a separate object at the end of the output array."}	blake3:mWRy-P5ho-gu6PnfZgfD5PEXu2gAk3yhCPc8WBz-i_I
1778523760598103	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvSg		item.update	bn-131	{"field":"description","value":"Translate OpenRouter auth failures into a clear next-step message.\n\nScope:\n- On HTTP 401 from /activity or /credits, exit code 2 with stderr message: \"OpenRouter rejected this key (<masked>). The /activity endpoint requires a Management API key, not an inference key. Create one at https://openrouter.ai/settings/keys under Management Keys.\"\n- 403, 429, and other 4xx/5xx: surface upstream message verbatim (no 401-styled rewording).\n- Distinguish exit codes: 0 (ok or no data), 2 (auth), 3 (network), 1 (other).\n\nAcceptance:\n- Stub server returning 401 produces the exact phrase above to stderr; exit code = 2.\n- Unmasked key never appears in stderr or stdout (grep test across the test suite).\n- HTTP 403 passes through with the body intact and a distinct exit code (1)."}	blake3:Vlu-M0up28U6l1QMVD71-GvY8VIzntGyrUzWioHbUUg
1778523760617470	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvSw		item.update	bn-3gz	{"field":"description","value":"Open or create ~/.cache/reckon/index.sqlite and apply the schema in notes/plan.md section 8.\n\nScope:\n- crates/reckon-core/src/cache.rs: fn open_cache(path: &Path) -> rusqlite::Connection.\n- Create tables source_files and events plus indices (events_month).\n- Track PRAGMA user_version. Bumping the version runs migrations idempotently.\n- Enable WAL mode (PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL).\n\nAcceptance:\n- First-run creates the file at ~/.cache/reckon/ (mkdir -p parent), user_version = 1.\n- Re-running on an existing v1 cache is a no-op (no migration writes).\n- A test that sets user_version = 0 triggers the migration on next open, ending at user_version = 1.\n- Concurrent opens (two processes) do not corrupt the DB (WAL handles this)."}	blake3:DAjeyuQ7_f0Tu_KhKNqBHOx_et6mME-d-xvYv4m_JEo
1778523760637113	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvTA		item.update	bn-hxj	{"field":"description","value":"On a fresh cache, persist every event the Sink receives.\n\nScope:\n- Sink batches events into transactions of 5000 rows. INSERT OR IGNORE INTO events (..., dedup_key, ...) keyed on (source, dedup_key).\n- After each Reader signals end-of-scan, INSERT/UPDATE source_files with final (path, mtime_ns, size_bytes, last_offset=size_at_eof).\n- Each batch is a single BEGIN..COMMIT to avoid per-row fsync.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Cold scan of a 1000-event fixture completes in < 200ms and yields exactly 1000 rows in events.\n- Duplicate events within one scan (same source+dedup_key) result in one row (INSERT OR IGNORE working).\n- After the scan, source_files has one row per file scanned, with last_offset matching the file size."}	blake3:dgB0pu4Olv6yhLxt_aWGH6y5vBXAtEJJQ_uu0W7xwoo
1778523760658446	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvTQ		item.update	bn-3n4	{"field":"description","value":"Skip work on files that have not changed; resume tail-reads on growing JSONL files.\n\nScope:\n- Before opening any JSONL: stat. If (mtime_ns, size_bytes) match the source_files row -> skip.\n- If size grew: open, seek to last_offset, parse new bytes, then UPDATE source_files SET last_offset = current_size, mtime_ns = new_mtime.\n- If size shrank or mtime is older: treat as a rewritten file. Re-scan from offset 0; old dedup_keys stay in events.\n- For Pi: short-circuit using session-index.sqlite last_modified before even statting the file.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Cold-scan a 100-event JSONL, append 20 events, warm-scan: exactly 20 new events emitted.\n- Warm-scan with unchanged mtime+size: 0 events emitted; 0 file opens (verified by a tracing probe).\n- Truncated-then-rewritten file: full re-scan happens; events table contains both old and new dedup_keys (no GC in v1; acceptable)."}	blake3:s7oVKy2nDT7g2sCosViUeW_NPOn5VVavRuhauPdpVuA
1778523760677321	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvTg		item.update	bn-2qk	{"field":"description","value":"Per-source warm-run handling for the two non-JSONL sources.\n\nScope:\n- OpenCode: store the max(created) seen as source_files.last_offset (re-purposed as \"last cursor\", path = \"<sqlite>\"). Warm SQL: WHERE created > ?1.\n- OpenRouter: NEVER trust cache for the rolling 30-day window. Always re-fetch every day. Use INSERT OR REPLACE on dedup_key — upstream usage can change as billing finalises.\n- The Reader::cache_strategy() function (defined in bn-d7t) routes each source to the right warm path: JsonlTail (bn-3n4), SqlCursor (this bone for OpenCode), NeverCache (this bone for OpenRouter).\n\nAcceptance:\n- OpenCode warm scan with no new rows: 0 events emitted, < 50ms.\n- OpenRouter warm scan: still issues 30 HTTP requests; rows with changed `usage` are updated (REPLACE).\n- Unit test verifying each Source maps to the correct CacheStrategy enum variant."}	blake3:EFndB2XdhNqiTe9vXxb465cVdpFQQcMVAqTy3ZyQUyU
1778523760699455	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvTw		item.update	bn-2v6	{"field":"description","value":"Acceptance test for the cache work as a whole.\n\nScope:\n- Add a hyperfine-driven benchmark script in scripts/bench-warm.sh: hyperfine --warmup 3 \"cargo run --release -- --month 2026-04 --source claude,codex,gemini,pi,opencode\".\n- Use the users actual cache if populated; else seed a synthetic events table with ~50k rows across a year.\n- Strip OpenRouter from the benchmarked source set (it is network-bound by design).\n\nAcceptance:\n- p95 wall-clock on this machine (AMD Linux box, warm cache) is < 200ms.\n- A regression PR that pushes warm time over 300ms fails the bench check.\n- README documents how to run the bench locally."}	blake3:Q0PpDEZpk6G6anPgN158Kk83ot2lAfcVlCg72YlbbSs
1778523760719195	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvUA		item.update	bn-vcy	{"field":"description","value":"Optional network refresh of the pricing snapshot.\n\nScope:\n- On startup (after cache open, before readers fan out), check ~/.cache/reckon/pricing.json mtime.\n- If older than 7 days or missing: spawn a side-task that GETs https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BerriAI/litellm/main/model_prices_and_context_window.json and writes via atomic temp -> rename.\n- Do NOT block the main pipeline. If readers finish first, render with whatever pricing was already loaded.\n- On fetch failure: single stderr warning; continue with existing file (or vendored fallback).\n- Loaded pricing = cached file UNION vendored fallback, cached takes precedence on key collisions.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Test: stale (>8d) pricing.json triggers the fetcher and rewrites the file.\n- Test: fresh pricing.json makes no HTTP call.\n- Test: fetcher failure (stub server 500) leaves the existing file untouched and prints exactly one warning to stderr."}	blake3:vgiEAw6In45x-0T4h_3i6RuPwFqSlwO79Rdk1G_qaLg
1778523760740341	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvUQ		item.update	bn-1re	{"field":"description","value":"Hard-disable the LiteLLM fetcher.\n\nScope:\n- clap flag --offline on the root command.\n- When set: skip the bn-vcy fetcher entirely. Pricing loads from ~/.cache/reckon/pricing.json if present, else vendored fallback.\n- Document the trade-off in --help: newer models may price at $0 if neither cache nor fallback has them; they appear in the unknown-pricing warning.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon --offline` opens no sockets to GitHub or LiteLLM (verified under strace -e openat,connect grepping for raw.githubusercontent.com).\n- With only the vendored fallback (no cache file), --offline still produces a sensible table for the top 5 models on this machine."}	blake3:TFt_-91-JBK5qJggDfVmyJGIwT8BKkmp5Bkxr2cWOy8
1778523760762587	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvUg		item.update	bn-3e9	{"field":"description","value":"Maintenance command for refreshing the checked-in fallback.\n\nScope:\n- crates/xtask/src/main.rs handles subcommand `vendor-pricing`.\n- Downloads the LiteLLM URL, pretty-prints the JSON to crates/reckon-core/assets/pricing-fallback.json.\n- Pretty-printing keeps diffs readable in code review.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `cargo xtask vendor-pricing` works from a fresh clone with network.\n- Resulting file passes the parser test from bn-l2h.\n- README mentions running this before each release tag."}	blake3:0BjQUPcbhf9l2AR97HhzOMcZMYLk6x6TBSuF7xhwZjo
1778523760785141	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvUw		item.update	bn-1sk	{"field":"description","value":"Do not spam one warning per unknown-model row.\n\nScope:\n- During aggregation, collect HashSet<ModelSlug> of slugs with no pricing match (neither cached nor vendored).\n- After the table, if non-empty, print one stderr line: \"warning: priced at $0 (no pricing data): slug-a, slug-b, slug-c\".\n- Sorted, capped at first 10; if more, append \"(and N more)\".\n\nAcceptance:\n- Run with 100 events across 3 unknown slugs: exactly one stderr line, slugs sorted.\n- Run with 0 unknown slugs: no warning line at all.\n- Warning goes to stderr (so `reckon --json | jq` is unaffected)."}	blake3:N79RM9Fxu1EGutyDJiOEJuvL-j_CGMf0fqUPgi1x_zo
1778523760806438	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvVA		item.update	bn-ojx	{"field":"description","value":"Date-range flags.\n\nScope:\n- clap derive: --month <YYYY-MM> single-month override; --since <YYYY-MM> and --until <YYYY-MM> inclusive range.\n- Validate ordering: since <= until.\n- --month is mutually exclusive with --since/--until.\n- No flags = every month present in the cache, newest first.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon --month 2026-05` shows only that month.\n- `reckon --since 2026-01 --until 2026-04` shows exactly 4 months (Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr).\n- `reckon --month 2026-05 --since 2026-01` exits non-zero with a clear conflict message.\n- `reckon --since 2026-04 --until 2026-01` exits non-zero with \"--since must be <= --until\"."}	blake3:nzHz2glT_qF5l5iJf9Ga9TaiRy-mV907UfMlnsdZrDw
1778523760827340	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvVQ		item.update	bn-3rz	{"field":"description","value":"Restrict which Readers run.\n\nScope:\n- --source claude,codex,gemini,pi,opencode,openrouter (comma-separated; validated against Source enum).\n- Unknown name: hard error listing valid values.\n- Default: each source whose data dir exists on disk (or, for openrouter, whose key resolves).\n- Auto-detection happens before readers fan out and is summarised in --verbose.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon --source claude` runs only the Claude reader.\n- `reckon --source claude,codex` runs both; no other-source rows appear.\n- `reckon --source foo` exits non-zero with \"unknown source: foo (valid: claude, codex, gemini, opencode, openrouter, pi)\"."}	blake3:B9wO-xrg4BxYrcE_U-AZq62atse2WFMBsuDTVn9TPM0
1778523760846990	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvVg		item.update	bn-2q8	{"field":"description","value":"Compose the group-by used by the aggregator and renderer.\n\nScope:\n- --by takes a comma-separated list: source, model, provider, project. Default source,model.\n- Aggregator group key is the tuple of requested dimensions; renderer drops columns for omitted dimensions.\n- Month is always implicit; per-month total row is always rendered.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon --by source` collapses model; one row per (month, source).\n- `reckon --by model` collapses source; per-model totals across sources.\n- `reckon --by source,model,project` renders all three breakdown columns.\n- `reckon --by foo` exits non-zero with a clear error."}	blake3:nkYKzzduodvWWZwMAZ8cj_cRUn5ufqGQsX0Wd8Vjyh8
1778523760872068	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvVw		item.update	bn-3r7	{"field":"description","value":"Machine-readable variant of the table.\n\nScope:\n- Emit a JSON array, one object per displayed row: { month, source, model, provider, project, input, output, cache_read, cache_write, reasoning, cost_usd, known_cost_usd? } — known_cost_usd only on OpenRouter rows.\n- Field order is stable.\n- Suppress all chrome: no banner; warnings stay on stderr.\n- OpenRouter balance (bn-33k) appended as one extra object at the end with key \"openrouter_balance\".\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon --json | jq length` returns the right row count.\n- `reckon --json` is valid JSON parseable by `jq`, no leading/trailing junk.\n- With --json, no ANSI color codes appear in stdout regardless of TTY state."}	blake3:EFd3ni_vvAnQbGJzR3wqUt89ORslBc8dpctTkOellXY
1778523760891529	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvWA		item.update	bn-l6s	{"field":"description","value":"Colored output for humans; plain for pipes.\n\nScope:\n- Color via a tokio-free crate (nu-ansi-term or anstream). Detection: stdout isatty && env NO_COLOR not set.\n- --no-color flag forces plain. --color=always forces color even when piped.\n- All warnings (unknown-pricing, opencode-locked, etc.) respect the same color decision.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `reckon | cat` produces zero ANSI escape codes.\n- `reckon` to a TTY shows color (smoke test, not snapshot).\n- `NO_COLOR=1 reckon` to a TTY produces no color."}	blake3:bLlDcvDEsgXMkWV41kdZfUkAmRXDsUPe1W9bRf1gPdQ
1778523760912589	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvWQ		item.update	bn-3rj	{"field":"description","value":"Lock the renderers output so future changes are intentional.\n\nScope:\n- For each source, anonymised fixtures in tests/fixtures/<source>/. Build a deterministic UsageEvent set; render; insta::assert_snapshot.\n- Snapshot the pretty table AND the --json form separately.\n- insta::with_settings to redact time-dependent fields (e.g. OpenRouter balance.fetched_at).\n- cargo-insta added to CI; missing/changed snapshots fail the build.\n\nAcceptance:\n- `cargo insta test` passes from a clean clone after `cargo insta accept`.\n- Removing or renaming a column fails the snapshot.\n- Fixture set covers >= 1 row per source and >= 1 month boundary."}	blake3:szh2a_9jkJkr5qPh8DVMVy9Vn-oLS8CECX84cQt1Zdk
1778523760931946	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvWg		item.link	bn-l2x	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-ive"}	blake3:Lt4i_nZrCCxb9UOf-BUlaPUMrOe_Aw16IB5rPABUDNA
